histological exam was performed in four patients who died (1 case) or had 
homograft-related complications (3 cases). The results of this study indicated 
that cryopreserved arterial homografts could be a promising alternative when 
below-knee revascularization is required in patients lacking suitable greater 
saphenous vein, especially in those with limited life expectancy, but despite 
early acceptable results, many aspects must be clarified. Close follow-up is 
mandatory.

