Improving end-of-life care: what providers need to know.

Makosky NR, Lynn J.

There is no question that advanced medicine and improved public health have made 
living into old age a reality for many people. Currently the average life 
expectancy for women is 79 years; for men the age is 73. Many of us can 
reasonably assume that we will live longer lives than did our parents and 
grandparents. Unfortunately, many also assume that modern medical care has 
improved care for people in the last phase of life. However, this may not be the 
case.

